-- Shanghai index hits 8-month high on strength in large-cap shares
-- By Chen Yixin and Pete Sweeney
-- Fri Aug 15, 2014 03:13AM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, Aug 15 (Reuters) - Shanghai shares rose 0.9 percent to an 8-month high on Friday, supported by a rebound in large-cap shares and some solar companies after Beijing said it will halt imports of processed polysilicon.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> was up 0.9 percent at 2,226.73 points. It rose 1.5 percent this week.  The CSI300 <.CSI300> of leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings was up 1.1 percent for the day and 1.3 percent this week. Blue-chip shares, including brokerages and insurance companies, were the biggest index supporters on Friday. Ping An Insurance (Group) Company of China <601318.SS> advanced 1.6 percent and Guo Yuan Securities Company Limited <000728.SZ> jumped by the 10 percent daily limit.